{"title":"Crust Bikes New Evasion Trail 140","link":"https://theradavist.com/crust-bikes-evasion-trail-140/","date":1704726785000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00512.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00512.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00512.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00512.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00512.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00512.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00512.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00512.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><em>You might not expect the co-owner of <a href=\"https://crustbikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Crust Bikes</a> to have oftentimes preferred a moto for solo touring over a bicycle but it’s true. Matt from Crust Bikes is a longtime lover of mini motos and often found himself on them when he was touring around the world. One bike in particular always met his fancy; the Postie bike. Although, he preferred the bike not only for its whopping 7 horsepower but its step-through design, which inspired the new <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/archive-re-up-2015-matt-and-his-crust-bikes-evasion-prototype/\" target=\"_blank\">Evasion</a> Trail 140. Matt gave us a sneak peek at this new all steel chassis tourer, so let’s check out the forthcoming Evasion Trail 140 below…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/8374338597_76819a37aa_o.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/8374338597_76819a37aa_o.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/8374338597_76819a37aa_o.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/8374338597_76819a37aa_o.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/8374338597_76819a37aa_o.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/8374338597_76819a37aa_o.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/8374338597_76819a37aa_o.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/8374338597_76819a37aa_o.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Matt from Crust Bikes has a long love affair with step-through bikes, but the kinda step thru that always attracted me was the motor variety, specifically the mighty Postie bike, or as its also called the Honda trail 90 &amp; 110. A 7-horse power thunder bolt between ya legs.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/snow-1.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/snow-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/snow-1.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/snow-1.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/snow-1.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/snow-1.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/snow-1.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/snow-1.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/IMG_3557.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/IMG_3557.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/IMG_3557.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/IMG_3557.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/IMG_3557.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/IMG_3557.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/IMG_3557.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/IMG_3557.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Back when Matt was traveling around the world a lot, if no one could join him on the trip, he would more often then not choose the Postie bike or some other small displacement motorcycle over a bicycle for its ability to cover more ground, but still force me to stay in the slow lane. For as we all know the shoulder is the real slow lane.</p>\n<p>As for Matt, long length solo-bicycle touring was a little boring and taxing on his sanity; so the ability to get out of a place or section of road that was soul crushing semi-quickly was nice.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00522.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00522.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00522.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00522.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00522.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00522.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00522.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00522.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>The aesthetic of the Postie just always put a smile on his face. So he figured it was high time to make a Crust step thru. Behold the Evasion Trail 140.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00478.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00478.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00478.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00478.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00478.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00478.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00478.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00478.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00477.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00477.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00477.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00477.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00477.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00477.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00477.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00477.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00480.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00480.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00480.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00480.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00480.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00480.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00480.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00480.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Now, is it as amazingly good looking as the Honda Trail 90? Well that is a matter of opinion, but in Matt’s opinion, that would be a no.  Does it come with a rip ya arms off 7 HP? Well, no. Its called the Evasion trail 140 because Matt averages 140 watts.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00491.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00491.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00491.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00491.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00491.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00491.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00491.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00491.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00488.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00488.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00488.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00488.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00488.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00488.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00488.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00488.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00489.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00489.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00489.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00489.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00489.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00489.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00489.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00489.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Does it put a huge smile on Matt and everyone at Crust’s face? Hell yeah it does! That is what any bike is about, motor or pedal.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00486.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00486.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00486.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00486.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00486.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00486.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00486.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00486.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00484.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00484.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00484.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00484.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00484.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00484.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00484.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00484.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00518.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00518.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00518.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00518.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00518.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00518.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00518.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00518.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>There is absolutely nothing groundbreaking about this bike, it is an Evasion rear end with a longer front end, and the geometry is the same as the Evasion aside from the standover, and it has a slightly longer reach. They have been stretched out in the front a fair amount. Three sizes will be available… eventually.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00503.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00503.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00503.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00503.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00503.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00503.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00503.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/DSC00503.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Build Spec:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Wheels BB</li>\n<li>Appleman cranks</li>\n<li>Nitto X Crumb works KT bar</li>\n<li>Crust hold ya horses grips</li>\n<li>Sram GX AXS</li>\n<li>Berthound saddle</li>\n<li>Tech 77 levers</li>\n<li>Palm oil brakes</li>\n<li>Crust headset</li>\n<li>Crust Pedals</li>\n<li>Carbon Ti hubs</li>\n<li>A chain</li>\n<li>Nitto X Crust Stem</li>\n<li>Rod Stuart bag support</li>\n<li>Fabs chest bag</li>\n<li>Nitto and a Velo Orange bottle cage</li>\n<li>A seatpost</li>\n<li>Some brake cables</li>\n<li>26 x 3 surly Knard tyres</li>\n<li>Fuel ration 60/1 60 marshmallows for every meat pie</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Keep an eye on <a href=\"https://crustbikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Crust Bikes</a> and <a href=\"https://www.heapsgoodgarage.com.au/\" target=\"_blank\">Heaps Good Garage</a> for the Evasion 140 to drop soon! </em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/crust-bikes-evasion-trail-140/\">Crust Bikes New Evasion Trail 140</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"e33b386dee80690878e4b2285f35219c9c07b0a4ef552487814cf9a189c1cf22","category":"Cycling"}